%% paper/replicate.run_rag + rag_utils + rag_eval — extrinsic validation (Tables 4–5)
%% Compares Adaptive ("best") vs two fixed baselines on a generated QA set.
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Sel as analysis.output_best_chunks
    participant QA as QA generation (GPT-4.1)
    participant Idx as Haystack index
    participant Ret as Hybrid retriever
    participant Gen as Answer LLM
    participant Judge as LLM judges (DeepEval)

    Note over Sel: 3 chunk sets:<br/>best (adaptive) · langchain_default · page
    Sel->>QA: parsed docs → 3 QA pairs/doc
    QA-->>Idx: generated_qa_pairs.json (99 queries)

    loop for each of the 3 chunk sets
        Sel->>Idx: chunks → embed (Qwen3-Embedding-4B)
        Idx->>Ret: document_store.json
        Ret->>Ret: BM25 + dense → join → rerank<br/>(snowflake-arctic-embed-l-v2.0)
        Ret->>Gen: top-k context per query
        Gen->>Judge: answer ONLY from context
        Judge->>Judge: Retrieval Completeness (0/1/2 → 0/.5/1)<br/>+ Answer Correctness
    end

    Note over Judge: Adaptive wins:<br/>Retrieval Completeness 67.7 vs 58.1 / 59.1<br/>Answer Correctness 78.0 vs 70.1 / 73.3<br/>(Wilcoxon p < 0.05)
